I've rebased to latest code and pulled back to use gflags 2.2.0 (which seems to have Bazel rules). I'm now trying to build this locally.

```
test/cpp/util/grpc_tool.cc:43:27: fatal error: gflags/gflags.h: No such file or directory
 #include <gflags/gflags.h>
                           ^
```

I think we will want to pull in newer gflags.

The latest gflags commit 
https://github.com/gflags/gflags/commit/30dbc81fb5ffdc98ea9b14b1918bfe4e8779b26e seems like it may be addressing this very issue. Maybe we can get @schuhschuh to cut a new release if that is the criteria? My original PR definitely pulled the latest commit and it worked.
